item.content:encoded:
Welcome to my Porfolio

My name is Dawn Watts and I am a student studying Creative Digital Media. Here is a small show case of some the the work I have done so far. I hope you enjoy and feel free to get in touch for any inquiries.

Now a little bit about myself. I am 21 years old and living and studying in Dublin. I am currently in IT Blanchardstown, in my third year doing Creative Digital Media. Here I have learnt some of the essentials to work within the digital media industry. I have done modules like Web development, web design, universal design, digital audio, Sound design, Drama filmmaking,Photography, Illustrator and photoshop skills, indesign skills Content Management systems, Branding, Multi media development and media within society.

With all these modules I have learned some valuable skills, some a little more obvious than others. Skills such as visual and audio editing, visual and audio design, website development and design, Communication and Team work skills, Understanding what goes behind a branding project as well as many more.

item.title: Graphic Design
item.dc:creator: dawnwatts
item.content:encoded:
ClockWork Orange Minimal poster

A simple poster made on Illustrator using simple shapes and two colors to give an illusion of a recognizable image.

VW Beetle Typography

This is a typography poster made for a small project in college. I made this using Photoshop. The Original VW beetle is my dream car so that was my inspiration. I used a blue font color as that is also the color I want the car to be in.

WellClik Logo

This was a branding project for a company called WellClik. For this project we had to come up with a suitable Logo to represent the brand. Wellclik is a booking app that connects Wellness Practitioners with regular customers in just 3 clicks. For my logo I was inspired by the Fuji mountains which are often linked with tranquility and a sun with represents a new day.

Dino

This is a cute little dinosaur character that I made in illustrator. His colorful and very textured skin would be very appealing for a children's character maybe in the future.

item.title: Wheres Cheap App
item.dc:creator: dawnwatts
item.content:encoded:
Wheres Cheap App

This was my second year project. There was four people on the team. Wheres cheap is an app that will let people know which bars, pubs and clubs are doing cheap drink promotions every day of the week. It has a "near me" section as well as separate  tabs for different types of bars etc.

Our Final Logo progress

So from left to right we see the first finalized logo down on paper. At this stage we had already picked our color pallet so that wasn't an issue.  from the paper logo we digitized it and decided that as the app itself is trendy, we wanted to have a logo that was also up to date with the latest graphic trends. With this in mind we settled on a "flat "design logo. You see this in the second picture. The last and final image you see the final image. It is similar to out second image but as you can see we added a flat design location pin to the top as we felt that our previous logo didnt get across the fact that our app was to let people know WHERE was cheap to drink.

Some Ads

These are just some ads that we made to keep the interest while building the app. Again trying to keep with what is "in" at the time of each post we made the star wars ones just as the new star wars movie was released. this kept people sharing for the humor.

Mister Clays Bad day.

 

https://vimeo.com/109128763

Stop Motion Anamation

This was a project I made in first year. The project was to create a short stop motion video using a iMovie.For mine I wanted to use clay and mould my character. In the end I took around 348 Photos.

DCU Marketing final year project

This was a marketing project for Final year DCU students. In this project they had to come up with an invention and then go through a full brand process. NVRwear is a razor cleaner that rinses the stubborn hairs out of a razor blade. For this project I filmed 80% of the advert and made the snapchat images (in photoshop). I was also heavily involved with the design of this product.
